headlines.description: — Scott Frost isn’t calling plays on offense this season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Northwestern rallies past Nebraska 31-28 in opener in Dublin

events.name: Idaho State Bengals at UNLV Rebels

headlines.description: — Doug Brumfield threw four touchdown passes, all in the first half, UNLV scored 35 points in the second quarter and the Rebels defeated Idaho State 52-21 in a season-opener on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brumfield, White lead UNLV's 52-21 rout of Idaho State

events.name: UConn Huskies at Utah State Aggies

headlines.description: — Logan Bonner threw three touchdown passes, Calvin Tyler Jr. added 161 yards rushing and Utah State defeated Connecticut 31-20 in a season-opener on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bonner's 3 TD passes lead Utah State past UConn 31-20

events.name: Wyoming Cowboys at Illinois Fighting Illini

headlines.description: — Chase Brown scored three touchdowns and rushed for 151 yards and Tommy DeVito completed 27 of 37 passes for 192 yards and two scores in his debut as Illinois breezed past Wyoming 38-6 in a season-opener on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown, DeVito lead Illinois past Wyoming 38-6 in opener

video.headline: Chase Brown scores his third TD of the day with ease

Nevada Wolf Pack at New Mexico State Aggies

headlines.description: — Devonte Lee ran for two second-quarter touchdowns and Nevada turned back New Mexico State 23-12 in a season opener on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lee sparks Nevada to 23-12 victory over NMSU in opener

events.name: North Texas Mean Green at UTEP Miners

headlines.description: — Austin Aune threw three touchdown passes, including two in a pivotal third quarter, and North Texas pulled away for a 31-13 victory over UTEP in a season opener on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Aune leads North Texas to 31-13 victory over UTEP in opener

events.name: Vanderbilt Commodores at Hawai'i Rainbow Warriors

headlines.description: — Mike Wright factored into four touchdowns and Vanderbilt used a 35-point third quarter to pull away from Hawaii 63-10 in a season opener on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wright ignites Vanderbilt in 63-10 romp over Hawaii
